::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:center
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:10.870 --> 00:00:12.450
Everyone!

3
00:00:12.450 --> 00:00:17.460
After we kick Kaido's ass,
we'll have a huge feast!

4
00:00:17.460 --> 00:00:18.960
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

5
00:00:18.960 --> 00:00:21.420
Outta my way, you weaklings!

6
00:00:35.680 --> 00:00:36.600
Jaggy!

7
00:00:36.600 --> 00:00:40.270
I won't let anyone else take Kaido's head!

8
00:00:40.270 --> 00:00:42.150
Right, Killer?

9
00:00:45.070 --> 00:00:46.360
Right.

10
00:00:57.500 --> 00:01:02.170
Kaido, you better make yourself presentable!

11
00:01:02.170 --> 00:01:07.010
'Cause I'm gonna take that ugly mug of yours
and mount it on the bow of my ship!

12
00:01:07.420 --> 00:01:08.420
Damn straight!

13
00:01:08.420 --> 00:01:11.680
How dare you turn Killer into a jolly guy?!

14
00:01:11.680 --> 00:01:15.180
We'll just become a jolly pirate crew, then!

15
00:01:15.180 --> 00:01:16.510
Stop it!

16
00:01:26.520 --> 00:01:29.280
Smell you later, Straw Hat!

17
00:01:29.280 --> 00:01:31.200
Hey, wait, Jaggy!

18
00:01:31.200 --> 00:01:32.450
That bastard!

19
00:01:36.620 --> 00:01:38.080
They're in a good mood!

20
00:01:41.330 --> 00:01:43.830
Jinbe! You know what to do!

21
00:01:43.830 --> 00:01:46.210
Keep up with Jaggy's ship!

22
00:01:48.210 --> 00:01:50.630
Sounds fun! Alright!

23
00:01:50.630 --> 00:01:52.220
Leave it to me!

24
00:01:52.220 --> 00:01:55.970
I'll catch up to that punk's ship in no time!

25
00:01:55.970 --> 00:01:58.560
About ship!

26
00:02:04.060 --> 00:02:06.310
Wow! Cool!

27
00:02:06.310 --> 00:02:08.780
You're a pro, Jinbe!

28
00:02:08.780 --> 00:02:11.280
After them!

29
00:02:15.070 --> 00:02:17.780
I'm gonna kick your ass!

30
00:02:17.780 --> 00:02:21.410
Just you wait, Kaido!

31
00:02:22.950 --> 00:02:25.820
Open up the borderless map, then

32
00:02:25.820 --> 00:02:29.020
Head for that unknown edge of the ocean

33
00:02:29.020 --> 00:02:33.410
LET’S SAIL ON right now, hoist your sails up high

34
00:02:33.410 --> 00:02:36.400
Riding on the wind

35
00:02:41.530 --> 00:02:45.740
DON’T GIVE UP, it’s time to finish what we started

36
00:02:45.930 --> 00:02:48.710
So don't you grow disheartened

37
00:02:49.020 --> 00:02:52.470
Laugh the tears away through the storm

38
00:02:52.670 --> 00:02:56.900
SHOUT IT OUT, when you feel down always remember

39
00:02:57.240 --> 00:02:59.500
That’s what your friends are there for

40
00:02:59.530 --> 00:03:01.660
Y’know there’s no point in fronting,

41
00:03:01.660 --> 00:03:05.580
your crew will always have your back

42
00:03:05.950 --> 00:03:09.680
Even in the face of utter darkness

43
00:03:09.910 --> 00:03:12.670
C’mon, BRAVE IT OUT We’ll be alright

44
00:03:12.970 --> 00:03:16.460
Together you know that we’ll never lose a fight

45
00:03:16.680 --> 00:03:19.450
Open up the borderless map, then

46
00:03:19.470 --> 00:03:22.310
Head for that unknown edge of the ocean

47
00:03:22.610 --> 00:03:26.890
All great journeys starts with a single step

48
00:03:26.960 --> 00:03:27.900
DREAMIN’ ON

49
00:03:27.900 --> 00:03:30.680
Open up the borderless map, then

50
00:03:30.680 --> 00:03:33.420
Raise the flag we swore to defend

51
00:03:33.570 --> 00:03:36.310
We’ll never stop until we’ve reached the top

52
00:03:36.380 --> 00:03:40.780
Just be true to yourself until the end

53
00:03:40.910 --> 00:03:45.620
Set sail and grab it, DREAMIN ON

54
00:03:57.550 --> 00:03:59.550
Now then, just as we planned...

55
00:03:59.550 --> 00:04:01.300
See you at the rear gate!

56
00:04:03.180 --> 00:04:05.600
<b>A Family Matter</b>

57
00:04:05.600 --> 00:04:07.100
Nin, nin!

58
00:04:11.060 --> 00:04:13.570
Sir Law! I am counting on you!

59
00:04:13.570 --> 00:04:15.030
Onward!

60
00:04:15.570 --> 00:04:17.030
Submerge!

61
00:04:17.030 --> 00:04:18.950
– Aye, aye, sir!
– Aye, aye, sir!

62
00:04:26.160 --> 00:04:28.870
Adjust trim, 30 degrees!

63
00:04:28.870 --> 00:04:30.830
Adjusting trim, 30 degrees!

64
00:04:35.210 --> 00:04:37.130
Sustain a depth of 100 meters!

65
00:04:37.130 --> 00:04:40.090
Captain! What's our course?!

66
00:04:40.470 --> 00:04:44.060
Full speed ahead to
the rear gate of Onigashima!

67
00:04:44.470 --> 00:04:46.470
– Aye, aye, sir!
– Aye, aye, sir!

68
00:04:53.820 --> 00:04:55.190
Everyone!

69
00:04:55.730 --> 00:04:58.190
Stay vigilant!

70
00:04:58.190 --> 00:05:00.110
Do not let your guard down!

71
00:05:00.490 --> 00:05:03.570
There could be an ambush any minute!

72
00:05:03.990 --> 00:05:06.740
Are you as sharp as I remember, Denjiro?

73
00:05:07.580 --> 00:05:12.120
Why bother surviving the last
two decades if not to hone my skills?

74
00:05:13.250 --> 00:05:14.710
I suppose you are, then!

75
00:05:16.210 --> 00:05:17.800
Let us finish this!

76
00:05:17.800 --> 00:05:19.130
Yes!

77
00:05:30.140 --> 00:05:31.890
There it is...

78
00:05:47.030 --> 00:05:49.620
So this is Onigashima!

79
00:05:53.120 --> 00:05:54.830
It's enormous!

80
00:05:55.330 --> 00:05:57.040
I've never seen it before.

81
00:05:57.040 --> 00:06:00.550
So this is Kaido's stronghold!

82
00:06:00.550 --> 00:06:02.550
Kin, look.

83
00:06:02.550 --> 00:06:03.800
I know...

84
00:06:03.800 --> 00:06:05.890
They are simply enjoying a banquet...

85
00:06:06.390 --> 00:06:09.270
without a single guard on duty.

86
00:06:09.890 --> 00:06:12.770
I suppose they have not received
Kanjuro's report yet...

87
00:06:12.770 --> 00:06:18.360
Or perhaps they have received it,
but they remain unconcerned...

88
00:06:18.940 --> 00:06:22.150
Regardless, we are fortunate...

89
00:06:22.150 --> 00:06:25.030
Now we can launch a surprise attack!

90
00:06:27.870 --> 00:06:31.080
Kaido's castle is pretty far inland, right?

91
00:06:31.080 --> 00:06:33.960
Yeah, looks like it!

92
00:06:33.960 --> 00:06:38.420
It's farther from here than we expected.

93
00:06:38.420 --> 00:06:41.800
If they haven't noticed yet,
we should attack quickly...

94
00:06:42.420 --> 00:06:43.380
What's that?

95
00:06:43.970 --> 00:06:45.180
Is that a guard?!

96
00:06:46.680 --> 00:06:48.970
What are those?

97
00:06:49.600 --> 00:06:50.970
Ships?

98
00:06:50.970 --> 00:06:53.230
Huh? You've gotta be kidding!

99
00:06:53.230 --> 00:06:55.390
I didn't hear anything about this!

100
00:06:55.390 --> 00:06:58.020
Why don't you guys take a nap?!

101
00:06:58.610 --> 00:07:01.400
Lethal Green Star!

102
00:07:11.290 --> 00:07:12.830
Sleepgrass!

103
00:07:16.920 --> 00:07:18.040
Oh?

104
00:07:18.040 --> 00:07:20.250
I thought I saw some people there...

105
00:07:28.720 --> 00:07:29.800
They just dozed off!

106
00:07:30.390 --> 00:07:32.350
Problem solved!

107
00:07:32.350 --> 00:07:34.020
Easy peasy!

108
00:07:38.190 --> 00:07:39.480
I see...

109
00:07:39.480 --> 00:07:42.730
I have a rough understanding of the plan...

110
00:07:42.730 --> 00:07:47.530
but if we moor this many
ships out in the open,

111
00:07:47.530 --> 00:07:51.620
it will surely alert our enemies!

112
00:07:51.990 --> 00:07:54.250
Prepare to disembark!

113
00:07:59.380 --> 00:08:01.000
What's going on?

114
00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:02.590
Don't tell me they...

115
00:08:02.920 --> 00:08:04.710
Destroy them!

116
00:08:12.220 --> 00:08:14.140
– What?!
– What?!

117
00:08:14.140 --> 00:08:16.850
What?! What?! What's all this about?!

118
00:08:16.850 --> 00:08:18.980
What are they doing?!

119
00:08:24.230 --> 00:08:27.320
You sank the ships to hide them?!

120
00:08:27.700 --> 00:08:31.200
But you can't sail them now!

121
00:08:31.620 --> 00:08:34.120
How are you guys gonna get back?!

122
00:08:34.120 --> 00:08:36.540
You just cut off your own escape!

123
00:08:38.790 --> 00:08:42.130
Sir Luffy, you need not worry.

124
00:08:44.130 --> 00:08:46.300
Let them all sink!

125
00:08:46.840 --> 00:08:49.090
For on this mission...

126
00:08:49.090 --> 00:08:50.630
we need no return ships!

127
00:08:55.680 --> 00:09:00.480
With that said, we must
advance. Please excuse us!

128
00:09:03.980 --> 00:09:06.940
Keep a low profile, men!

129
00:09:20.580 --> 00:09:23.540
What an incredible display of true resolve...

130
00:09:23.880 --> 00:09:26.840
from those samurai warriors.

131
00:09:27.760 --> 00:09:29.970
No hesitation...

132
00:09:29.970 --> 00:09:31.300
only determination...

133
00:09:31.840 --> 00:09:33.470
Win or die...

134
00:09:34.050 --> 00:09:37.890
There can be no arrogance
when taking on an Emperor!

135
00:09:39.180 --> 00:09:40.940
What if they wanna escape?!

136
00:09:41.310 --> 00:09:43.900
They'll be swallowed by the sea...

137
00:09:43.900 --> 00:09:44.730
Th-Then...

138
00:09:44.730 --> 00:09:45.860
Then...

139
00:09:45.860 --> 00:09:49.530
Does that mean we have to sink the Sunny?!

140
00:09:49.530 --> 00:09:50.990
No way, you dumbasses!

141
00:09:51.360 --> 00:09:53.860
A small number of ships can be hidden!

142
00:09:53.860 --> 00:09:56.450
You all should make your way ashore as well!

143
00:09:58.040 --> 00:10:00.960
Alright! I'll do it!

144
00:10:02.620 --> 00:10:03.500
What?!

145
00:10:03.500 --> 00:10:04.960
No way!

146
00:10:04.960 --> 00:10:06.840
Oh no!

147
00:10:06.840 --> 00:10:09.340
What is it, Carrot?

148
00:10:09.340 --> 00:10:10.800
Look!

149
00:10:13.720 --> 00:10:15.180
How did we not notice...?

150
00:10:15.180 --> 00:10:17.890
The shore is packed with enemies!

151
00:10:18.390 --> 00:10:20.020
No, it's not.

152
00:10:20.020 --> 00:10:20.640
Oh?

153
00:10:21.020 --> 00:10:22.810
Look at the other end of the bridge!

154
00:10:33.030 --> 00:10:35.820
Hey! What's with this?!

155
00:10:37.580 --> 00:10:39.490
It's what the enemy wears.

156
00:10:40.160 --> 00:10:42.160
Do you like it?

157
00:10:44.080 --> 00:10:46.420
That's one of my special techniques!

158
00:10:46.960 --> 00:10:50.630
Garb-Garb Kin's Clothing Company!

159
00:10:55.760 --> 00:10:56.720
It appears...

160
00:10:57.720 --> 00:10:59.680
some mighty pirates stand before me.

161
00:11:01.560 --> 00:11:04.520
You may invade this island as you like...

162
00:11:05.190 --> 00:11:06.980
but we face a formidable force!

163
00:11:07.520 --> 00:11:09.400
They outnumber us five to one.

164
00:11:10.320 --> 00:11:13.400
So I advise you to take
advantage of those disguises!

165
00:11:15.650 --> 00:11:17.160
Good thinking.

166
00:11:17.160 --> 00:11:21.540
We just wanna take down Kaido.
We don't have time for all the lackeys...

167
00:11:22.910 --> 00:11:24.160
Let's go!

168
00:11:24.160 --> 00:11:24.870
Yeah.

169
00:11:26.500 --> 00:11:27.880
Sir Luffy!

170
00:11:27.880 --> 00:11:30.670
Perhaps you should all pass through it as well!

171
00:11:30.670 --> 00:11:33.260
Yeah! That looks like fun!

172
00:11:40.800 --> 00:11:42.390
I'm gonna do it, too!

173
00:11:44.520 --> 00:11:45.600
Transform!

174
00:11:46.230 --> 00:11:47.480
Hup!

175
00:11:48.230 --> 00:11:49.440
Cool!

176
00:11:49.440 --> 00:11:51.440
Ta-da!

177
00:11:52.780 --> 00:11:55.280
Chobro! You look amazing!

178
00:11:55.280 --> 00:11:56.740
I'm going through, too!

179
00:12:06.870 --> 00:12:11.500
Nami! You're even more tantalizing!

180
00:12:11.880 --> 00:12:13.460
Now let me try it!

181
00:12:20.340 --> 00:12:23.220
How do I look?

182
00:12:23.220 --> 00:12:24.600
Same as usual.

183
00:12:25.270 --> 00:12:28.690
Don't you even care
enough to make fun of me?

184
00:12:28.690 --> 00:12:31.900
Robin, you're such a badass beauty!

185
00:12:31.900 --> 00:12:33.650
We're gonna do it, too!

186
00:12:39.030 --> 00:12:40.990
– Yay!
– Yay!

187
00:12:40.990 --> 00:12:43.240
Super!

188
00:12:43.660 --> 00:12:46.660
Now, since they were made by my technique,

189
00:12:46.660 --> 00:12:51.630
once you remove or tear them,
your original kimono will reappear!

190
00:12:54.920 --> 00:12:56.510
My fellow warriors!

191
00:12:56.880 --> 00:13:00.720
This is Onigashima, Kaido's stronghold!

192
00:13:01.140 --> 00:13:06.970
Avoid unnecessary battles whenever possible,
and try to reach the castle for the final battle!

193
00:13:09.770 --> 00:13:11.810
Good luck!

194
00:13:18.440 --> 00:13:19.950
That hits the spot!

195
00:13:19.950 --> 00:13:23.570
Now that we're free from
the ghosts of the Kozuki Clan,

196
00:13:23.570 --> 00:13:27.450
this booze tastes absolutely divine!

197
00:13:33.790 --> 00:13:35.880
Orochi is feeling carefree.

198
00:13:36.210 --> 00:13:41.470
Thanks to the spy Kanjuro informing
him of the Red Scabbards' plans,

199
00:13:41.470 --> 00:13:46.600
he conjured a foolproof plan
to counter their insurrection.

200
00:13:48.560 --> 00:13:51.600
Their rendezvous point is Tokage Port!

201
00:13:51.600 --> 00:13:54.730
Destroy all routes that lead there!

202
00:13:54.730 --> 00:13:56.320
<b>Great Bridge

Between

Kuri and Udon</b>

203
00:13:56.320 --> 00:13:57.860
<b>Great Bridge

Between Ringo

and Hakumai</b>

204
00:13:58.820 --> 00:14:01.450
<b>Itachi Port

Kuri</b>

205
00:14:01.450 --> 00:14:05.410
The Red Scabbards are scattered
and helpless! Be sure you kill them all!

206
00:14:11.000 --> 00:14:15.330
He will no longer be tormented
by the ghosts of the Kozuki Clan.

207
00:14:16.590 --> 00:14:20.260
<b>Onigashima</b>

208
00:14:18.210 --> 00:14:20.920
However, at Onigashima...

209
00:14:20.920 --> 00:14:23.760
<b>The Raid Has Begun</b>

210
00:14:21.880 --> 00:14:23.760
The raid has begun!

211
00:14:27.640 --> 00:14:31.100
<b>Eastern
Forces</b>

212
00:14:28.970 --> 00:14:31.100
The eastern forces led by Kin'emon.

213
00:14:35.940 --> 00:14:39.150
<b>Southern
Forces</b>

214
00:14:37.020 --> 00:14:39.150
The southern forces led by Denjiro.

215
00:14:39.820 --> 00:14:43.150
Combined, there are more than 5,000 troops.

216
00:14:46.870 --> 00:14:50.040
<b>Polar Tang</b>

217
00:14:52.040 --> 00:14:54.040
The pirate Law's submarine...

218
00:14:54.040 --> 00:14:56.380
<b>Law</b>
<b>Kaido's

Castle</b>
<b>Southern

Forces Eastern

Forces</b>

219
00:14:54.540 --> 00:14:58.000
has submerged with the
Red Scabbards samurai on board.

220
00:14:58.000 --> 00:15:02.340
Its course has been set for the castle
where Orochi and Kaido are.

221
00:15:06.050 --> 00:15:11.640
Their enemies are still unaware
of the 5,000 advancing troops.

222
00:15:12.140 --> 00:15:14.730
Hey, what's taking you so long?

223
00:15:14.730 --> 00:15:17.770
Hurry up, Franky!

224
00:15:17.770 --> 00:15:19.400
Everyone's already left.

225
00:15:19.400 --> 00:15:21.400
Give me a second.

226
00:15:21.400 --> 00:15:23.070
We'll catch up to them in no time...

227
00:15:23.070 --> 00:15:25.400
if we use this!

228
00:15:45.760 --> 00:15:50.300
Black Rhino FR-U4!

229
00:15:48.210 --> 00:15:50.300
<b>Black Rhino
FR-U4</b>

230
00:15:50.300 --> 00:15:51.760
Yay!

231
00:15:53.270 --> 00:15:56.100
I remember it from
the battle at Fishman Island!

232
00:15:56.480 --> 00:15:59.060
Not "it," Jinbe!

233
00:15:59.060 --> 00:16:00.940
Call this baby the Black Rhino!

234
00:16:00.940 --> 00:16:03.070
And there's another one!

235
00:16:10.780 --> 00:16:15.540
Brachio-Tank 5!

236
00:16:15.530 --> 00:16:17.740
<b>Brachio Tank 5</b>

237
00:16:20.580 --> 00:16:22.460
I'm in charge of this tank!

238
00:16:22.500 --> 00:16:22.660
<b>anderCho</b>
<b>manderChop</b>
<b>mmaopp</b>
<b>ommpe</b>
<b>Comper</b>

239
00:16:22.500 --> 00:16:25.540
<b>erC</b>

240
00:16:22.540 --> 00:16:25.540
<b>Cr</b>

241
00:16:22.670 --> 00:16:25.540
<b>andho</b>
<b>mp</b>
<b>oe</b>

242
00:16:22.960 --> 00:16:24.800
Commander Chopper, reporting!

243
00:16:25.550 --> 00:16:27.300
We're counting on you, Chopper!

244
00:16:27.300 --> 00:16:30.010
Great! We can get there safely!

245
00:16:30.010 --> 00:16:31.890
Chobro, you're so cool!

246
00:16:31.890 --> 00:16:33.850
You're in good hands!

247
00:16:35.350 --> 00:16:37.560
And I'm the gunner!

248
00:16:39.350 --> 00:16:40.350
Chopper!

249
00:16:40.350 --> 00:16:41.610
Usopp!

250
00:16:41.610 --> 00:16:42.730
Franky!

251
00:16:42.730 --> 00:16:45.940
<b>We're here!</b>

252
00:16:43.650 --> 00:16:45.280
– We're here!
– We're here!

253
00:16:47.110 --> 00:16:49.610
Now we're all ready!

254
00:16:50.490 --> 00:16:52.240
Where's Luffy?

255
00:16:52.240 --> 00:16:53.120
Well...

256
00:16:53.120 --> 00:16:58.370
Eustass Kid and his crew
headed straight into the island, so...

257
00:16:58.370 --> 00:16:59.410
Okay!

258
00:16:59.410 --> 00:17:01.040
I'm gonna go stop them!

259
00:17:01.040 --> 00:17:02.330
Don't worry!

260
00:17:04.420 --> 00:17:07.090
– He's only gonna make things worse!
– He's only gonna make things worse!

261
00:17:07.090 --> 00:17:08.840
Why didn't you stop him?!

262
00:17:08.840 --> 00:17:11.800
Roronoa Zoro said the same, but then...

263
00:17:11.800 --> 00:17:14.720
Luffy's only gonna make things worse!

264
00:17:14.720 --> 00:17:16.140
I'm gonna go stop him!

265
00:17:18.100 --> 00:17:20.730
– He'll just get lost in there!
– He'll just get lost in there!

266
00:17:20.730 --> 00:17:22.690
Is that so...?

267
00:17:22.690 --> 00:17:24.820
Forget about that moron!

268
00:17:24.820 --> 00:17:29.700
Let's go on a ride through
the battlefield, Nami!

269
00:17:35.030 --> 00:17:36.330
It's full!

270
00:17:37.700 --> 00:17:38.910
Get out, Usopp!

271
00:17:39.330 --> 00:17:41.620
Damn you! You're in heaven!

272
00:17:41.620 --> 00:17:44.460
I'm sorry you can't aim like me!

273
00:17:44.460 --> 00:17:45.590
Get over it!

274
00:17:50.720 --> 00:17:52.220
How about you ride with me?

275
00:17:52.220 --> 00:17:53.220
Can I?

276
00:17:53.220 --> 00:17:54.300
I'd be happy to.

277
00:17:55.470 --> 00:17:57.430
Okay, I'm ready.

278
00:17:58.180 --> 00:17:59.430
You?!

279
00:17:59.430 --> 00:18:01.520
What's wrong with a little bromance?

280
00:18:03.230 --> 00:18:04.810
Alright, fine.

281
00:18:06.860 --> 00:18:08.030
Commander Chopper!

282
00:18:08.030 --> 00:18:08.820
Yeah?

283
00:18:08.820 --> 00:18:12.490
Meet me at the back of the island,
and we'll dock these vehicles together.

284
00:18:12.490 --> 00:18:13.950
Good luck!

285
00:18:13.950 --> 00:18:15.410
"Docking"!

286
00:18:17.580 --> 00:18:20.040
Super!

287
00:18:20.580 --> 00:18:21.620
Roger!

288
00:18:27.460 --> 00:18:31.550
I feel like a rock star!

289
00:18:31.550 --> 00:18:34.590
Are you a haunted doll or something?!

290
00:18:35.390 --> 00:18:36.970
We should go, too!

291
00:18:38.350 --> 00:18:41.020
Robin my love!

292
00:18:41.020 --> 00:18:42.980
Come with me!

293
00:18:43.310 --> 00:18:45.270
No thanks.

294
00:18:45.270 --> 00:18:48.190
You'll get dusty on top of the tank.

295
00:18:49.480 --> 00:18:51.610
Shall we walk?

296
00:18:51.610 --> 00:18:52.570
Sure.

297
00:18:57.240 --> 00:19:00.080
You guys are as lively as ever.

298
00:19:00.080 --> 00:19:02.620
In a battle where everyone's pumped up,

299
00:19:02.620 --> 00:19:05.460
it's key to have someone
who can observe things calmly.

300
00:19:05.460 --> 00:19:06.880
You're so mature.

301
00:19:06.880 --> 00:19:08.090
It's quite reassuring.

302
00:19:08.090 --> 00:19:11.710
I want to be helpful in my
first battle as part of this crew!

303
00:19:20.810 --> 00:19:22.770
Hey! Keep walking!

304
00:19:26.020 --> 00:19:30.440
Kanjuro and the captive Momonosuke...

305
00:19:30.440 --> 00:19:36.030
have yet to reach Orochi,
just as Kin'emon surmised.

306
00:19:37.990 --> 00:19:40.490
I've never been down here before.

307
00:19:40.490 --> 00:19:42.450
I had no idea it was such a labyrinth.

308
00:19:42.950 --> 00:19:46.000
From the perspective of these
ignorant bit players,

309
00:19:46.000 --> 00:19:48.420
I'm still one of the Red Scabbards...

310
00:19:48.420 --> 00:19:53.300
I must report on Kin'emon
and the others as soon as possible.

311
00:19:53.300 --> 00:19:56.170
How can I get to Lord Orochi?!

312
00:20:04.640 --> 00:20:06.640
Dearest Lord Kaido!

313
00:20:06.640 --> 00:20:08.520
My word, it's been ages!

314
00:20:08.520 --> 00:20:10.770
Why do you keep talking like that?

315
00:20:15.490 --> 00:20:17.240
Are you drinking?

316
00:20:19.240 --> 00:20:21.490
There's no point in drinking with grunts.

317
00:20:21.910 --> 00:20:25.080
I wanna drink with you, Kaido!

318
00:20:25.080 --> 00:20:26.580
Yeah,

319
00:20:26.580 --> 00:20:28.210
sounds good.

320
00:20:28.210 --> 00:20:30.960
We'll go to the hall later.

321
00:20:30.960 --> 00:20:33.040
No standing on ceremony today.

322
00:20:33.420 --> 00:20:35.460
Why can't we go now?

323
00:20:35.960 --> 00:20:41.090
I was gonna introduce
you guys to Linlin first...

324
00:20:41.090 --> 00:20:43.180
but I heard she's changing.

325
00:20:43.180 --> 00:20:44.770
So let's see her later.

326
00:20:45.140 --> 00:20:51.730
Anyway, there was a small incident,
so I had to keep you guys waiting.

327
00:20:51.730 --> 00:20:53.360
You call this planning?!

328
00:20:53.360 --> 00:20:54.480
Hey! Stop!

329
00:20:54.480 --> 00:21:00.610
Yeah, I know, but it wasn't me that
summoned you guys in the first place.

330
00:21:00.610 --> 00:21:01.410
– Huh?!
– What?!

331
00:21:01.410 --> 00:21:04.240
Well, then who did?

332
00:21:07.000 --> 00:21:08.040
It was me.

333
00:21:10.000 --> 00:21:13.340
I summoned them here, Kaido.

334
00:21:13.340 --> 00:21:15.250
King...

335
00:21:15.250 --> 00:21:17.260
What the hell would you need from us?!

336
00:21:17.260 --> 00:21:19.800
You bastard! Why trick us?!

337
00:21:20.380 --> 00:21:24.350
If you had known it was at my request, some of you wouldn't have come.

338
00:21:24.350 --> 00:21:26.600
Who's-Who! Sasaki!

339
00:21:30.310 --> 00:21:31.520
You got that right.

340
00:21:32.020 --> 00:21:34.650
You two were once captains
of your own pirate crews...

341
00:21:35.070 --> 00:21:38.530
and now you're aiming for
our positions as the Superstars.

342
00:21:38.940 --> 00:21:41.950
In this group, merit decides the hierarchy.

343
00:21:41.950 --> 00:21:43.910
So of course we're aiming high!

344
00:21:44.320 --> 00:21:45.780
Know your place.

345
00:21:45.780 --> 00:21:47.910
Alright, enough!

346
00:21:48.330 --> 00:21:53.210
Why are you bickering on
the day of our special feast?

347
00:21:53.210 --> 00:21:56.250
King! Why did you summon them?

348
00:21:56.840 --> 00:22:01.590
Because I was the first to hear
about your little incident.

349
00:22:01.590 --> 00:22:02.880
So don't you need them?

350
00:22:03.800 --> 00:22:05.680
I do, indeed...

351
00:22:06.680 --> 00:22:08.270
Bao Huang!

352
00:22:08.850 --> 00:22:10.180
Coming!

353
00:22:14.310 --> 00:22:18.070
<b>Headliner Bao Huang

(Flying Squirrel SMILE)
Beast Pirates</b>

354
00:22:23.030 --> 00:22:25.240
What's my schedule today?

355
00:22:29.160 --> 00:22:36.460
Later at the Golden Festival stage
where Queen is performing now...

356
00:22:37.340 --> 00:22:43.340
the three Superstars
and Master Fukurokuju will...

357
00:22:43.340 --> 00:22:44.340
make a toast!

358
00:22:44.970 --> 00:22:49.510
Following that, Lord Orochi
and Lord Kaido will...

359
00:22:49.510 --> 00:22:50.810
give speeches!

360
00:22:51.310 --> 00:22:57.900
Then, when the Big Mom Pirates' ship arrives...

361
00:22:58.690 --> 00:23:04.280
Lord Kaido and Big Mom
will announce the world's strongest...

362
00:23:05.360 --> 00:23:08.780
pirate alliance!

363
00:23:09.660 --> 00:23:13.250
After that, Lord Kaido will make...

364
00:23:13.250 --> 00:23:18.540
an important announcement!

365
00:23:19.210 --> 00:23:20.250
That's it.

366
00:23:20.670 --> 00:23:22.420
An important announcement?!

367
00:23:22.420 --> 00:23:24.840
It's not like you to keep us waiting, Kaido.

368
00:23:24.840 --> 00:23:26.930
That's the very height of annoyance!

369
00:23:26.930 --> 00:23:29.430
Yeah, I know.

370
00:23:29.430 --> 00:23:32.310
But if I reveal it now,
it'll only cause confusion.

371
00:23:32.850 --> 00:23:36.810
Now, here is what I want you guys to do.

372
00:23:37.310 --> 00:23:43.440
My idiot son Yamato disappeared today,
so I want you to bring him to me!

373
00:23:43.440 --> 00:23:44.950
Whoa...

374
00:23:44.950 --> 00:23:46.660
That's quite a task.

375
00:23:46.660 --> 00:23:51.950
That must mean your announcement
involves Young Master Yamato?

376
00:23:51.950 --> 00:23:53.830
That's right.

377
00:23:53.830 --> 00:23:55.040
I see.

378
00:23:55.040 --> 00:23:57.830
What a pain! It's just a family matter!

379
00:23:57.830 --> 00:23:58.420
Hey!

380
00:23:58.960 --> 00:23:59.960
And...

381
00:24:00.590 --> 00:24:02.460
what if we bring him back safely?

382
00:24:02.460 --> 00:24:06.300
I'll give you the right to challenge
the Superstar of your choice.

383
00:24:07.430 --> 00:24:08.760
How's that?

384
00:24:08.760 --> 00:24:10.760
Seriously?

385
00:24:10.760 --> 00:24:12.010
I'll do it!

386
00:24:12.010 --> 00:24:14.470
I'm in, too!

387
00:24:15.100 --> 00:24:17.190
You don't mind, do you?

388
00:24:17.190 --> 00:24:18.480
No.No.

389
00:24:18.480 --> 00:24:19.900
Not at all!

390
00:24:25.070 --> 00:24:26.740
What is this?

391
00:24:26.740 --> 00:24:28.610
They made too much.

392
00:24:28.610 --> 00:24:30.620
Why bring it here?

393
00:24:30.620 --> 00:24:31.910
We had no choice!

394
00:24:31.910 --> 00:24:33.120
Jaggy!

395
00:24:33.120 --> 00:24:34.870
Where are you?!

396
00:24:34.870 --> 00:24:37.370
He doesn't even know about Oden's wish!

397
00:24:37.370 --> 00:24:39.080
Why did he go off on his own?!

398
00:24:40.500 --> 00:24:42.880
Hey! Have you seen Jaggy?!

399
00:24:42.880 --> 00:24:45.130
Jaggy? Who's that?

400
00:24:45.130 --> 00:24:48.840
If I get thinner, I'll be too popular

401
00:24:48.840 --> 00:24:51.220
So I don't get thinner, that's my kind of...

402
00:24:51.220 --> 00:24:52.430
funk!

403
00:24:52.430 --> 00:24:54.470
It's that balloon guy!

404
00:24:55.600 --> 00:24:56.730
You're late!

405
00:24:56.730 --> 00:24:58.310
Why don't you eat, too?

406
00:24:58.310 --> 00:24:59.060
Huh?

407
00:24:59.060 --> 00:25:00.480
This way! This way!

408
00:25:00.480 --> 00:25:01.440
Yeah.

409
00:25:02.860 --> 00:25:04.190
Wow!

410
00:25:04.190 --> 00:25:06.690
Everything looks so delicious!

411
00:25:06.690 --> 00:25:08.570
Why don't you chow down, too?

412
00:25:08.570 --> 00:25:10.070
Really?!

413
00:25:11.070 --> 00:25:14.450
The entire harvest from
Halcyon Farm is ours alone to enjoy!

414
00:25:15.160 --> 00:25:19.710
If the people of Okobore Town ate one bite,
they'd die of shock from the rich taste!

415
00:25:19.710 --> 00:25:21.120
Take it already!

416
00:25:21.120 --> 00:25:22.830
I told you I don't want it!

417
00:25:28.170 --> 00:25:30.220
Ouch! Ow, ow, ow!

418
00:25:30.220 --> 00:25:31.470
Hey, what's that?

419
00:25:31.470 --> 00:25:32.930
It's oshiruko!

420
00:25:32.930 --> 00:25:34.260
But we're drinking now!

421
00:25:34.260 --> 00:25:35.260
Screw you!

422
00:25:36.430 --> 00:25:37.390
Oshiruko?

423
00:25:37.390 --> 00:25:41.060
They made too much, so the rest is ours.

424
00:25:41.060 --> 00:25:42.060
Dumbass!

425
00:25:42.060 --> 00:25:44.060
It doesn't go with alcohol!

426
00:25:44.060 --> 00:25:45.770
There's plenty of stuff to eat!

427
00:25:46.320 --> 00:25:47.480
Just trash it!

428
00:25:47.480 --> 00:25:49.650
This soup is way too sweet!

429
00:25:49.650 --> 00:25:52.320
Let's dump it all over Okobore Town!

430
00:25:53.320 --> 00:25:54.570
Good idea!

431
00:25:54.570 --> 00:25:56.660
They'll happily lap it up off the ground!

432
00:26:12.880 --> 00:26:16.260
It's so yummy!

433
00:26:16.760 --> 00:26:20.060
This soup is so delicious!

434
00:26:20.060 --> 00:26:23.100
What? Is this your first time having it?!

435
00:26:23.100 --> 00:26:24.020
Yes!

436
00:26:24.020 --> 00:26:26.480
There's even mochi in it!

437
00:26:26.480 --> 00:26:29.070
What a fancy treat!

438
00:26:38.240 --> 00:26:41.620
This is the greatest day of my life!

439
00:26:43.920 --> 00:26:45.460
Damn beggars!

440
00:26:45.460 --> 00:26:48.250
Just be happy you're alive!
